📘 How to Use This RAG AI Teaching Assistant on Your Own Data

This project lets you build a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system over your own video content. Follow the steps below to index new videos and query them using a local LLM.

Step 1 – Add Your Videos

Place all your video files (e.g., .mp4) inside the videos/ directory.

videos/
  ├── lecture1.mp4
  ├── lecture2.mp4
  └── ...

Step 2 – Convert Videos to Audio (MP3)

Extract audio from all videos using FFmpeg:

video_to_mp3


This will generate .mp3 files inside the audios/ directory.

Step 3 – Transcribe Audio to JSON (Whisper)

Convert all MP3 files into structured JSON transcripts:

mp3_to_json


Each JSON file contains timestamped text chunks from the video.

Step 4 – Generate Embeddings (Vector Index)

Convert JSON transcripts into vector embeddings and store them as a searchable index:

preprocess_json


This step:

Loads all JSON files

Generates embeddings using bge-m3

Saves a vector database as embeddings.joblib

Step 5 – Ask Questions (RAG Inference)

Load the vector index and query it with natural language questions:

python process_incoming.py


The system:

Embeds your query

Retrieves the most relevant video chunks

Generates a grounded answer with timestamps using a local LLM

🔁 End-to-End Pipeline

Videos → Audio (MP3) → JSON Transcripts → Embeddings (Vectors) → RAG Prompt → LLM Answer